# 🌸 Happy Mother's Day Website

A magical, animated surprise website for Mom — built with pure HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
No frameworks needed. Just open `index.html` in VS Code Live Server or any browser.

---

## 📁 File Structure

```
mothers-day/
│
├── index.html       ← Main page (structure)
├── style.css        ← All styles & animations
├── script.js        ← Interactivity & effects
├── README.md        ← This file
│
└── photos/          ← 📸 Create this folder & add photos!
    ├── photo1.jpg
    ├── photo2.jpg
    ├── photo3.jpg
    ├── photo4.jpg
    ├── photo5.jpg
    └── photo6.jpg
```

---

## ✏️ How to Customize

### 1. Add Photos
- Create a folder called `photos/` inside the project folder
- Add your photos named `photo1.jpg` through `photo6.jpg`
- You can change photo captions in `index.html` — look for `<p class="photo-caption">`

### 2. Change the Children's Names
In `index.html`, search for:
- `[Child 1's Name]`
- `[Child 2's Name]`
- `[Child 3's Name]`
Replace these with the real names.

### 3. Write the Real Letters
In `index.html`, find the three `<div class="letter-body">` sections.
Each one has a comment: `<!-- ✏️ REPLACE THIS with Child X's real letter -->`
Replace the placeholder text with the actual letter from each child.

### 4. Update the Date
In `index.html`, find `May 11, 2025` inside the `<div class="date-badge">` and update it.

---

## 🚀 Upload to GitHub Pages

1. Create a new GitHub repository (e.g., `mothers-day`)
2. Upload all files (including the `photos/` folder)
3. Go to **Settings → Pages**
4. Set source to **main branch / root**
5. GitHub will give you a link like: `https://yourusername.github.io/mothers-day/`
6. Share that link with Mom! 🎉

---

## 🌟 Features
- 🌸 Falling petals animation
- ✨ Twinkling glitter on the hero
- 💌 3 animated envelopes that open to reveal letters
- 📸 Photo gallery with hover effects
- 🎀 Sparkle burst when opening letters
- 📱 Mobile responsive
- 💖 Pure HTML/CSS/JS — no dependencies!